This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Jing Yibu, southern weekend reporter

Southern weekend intern, Gong Roushan, Ye Zi

Editor in chief | Zhang Yue

On January 29,2020, a request for help went viral.

The request came from the village of Yuhu, which is under the jurisdiction of the Yulong Naxi Autonomous County Baisha, Taishan in Lijiang, Yunnan Province. As of 0000 hours on 3 February 2020,105 confirmed cases have been reported in Yunnan Province, including 7 in Lijiang. The village responded by calling for help as the country's epidemic of new-crown pneumonia was raging.

"At present, there is an urgent need for medical and epidemic prevention supplies... the whole city is sold out of face masks, and there are almost no effective protective supplies in the countryside, " the Post said. Because of the lack of protective supplies, the Yuhu village committee, while doing its protection publicity work, fear of cross-contamination.

According to the post, there are more than 1800 people in Yuhu village, and there is an urgent shortage of effective protection measures. Ask for help from several kinds of protective products including: Antiviral drug, protective goggles, masks and sterilization supplies.

In Nakhi people, the village is called "Wulukun" , which means "at the foot of the Snow Mountain. " . This is the nearest village to Jade Dragon Snow Mountain, and tourism is the main source of income for the local villagers. In November 2019, Yuhu village was included in the list of beautiful and leisure villages in China.

Every Spring Festival is the peak season of tourism in Yuhu village, where tourists from all over the country spend their holidays. But in the Spring Festival of 2020, a raging epidemic broke the village's tranquility.

On January 25th, the country was gripped by an epidemic. Under the deployment of the village committee, Yuhu village began to implement the "soft-sealed village. ". Village restaurants all closed, 49-year-old villagers Lu Qunzhi was afraid, want to close his grocery store, but failed. "The director said we couldn't close the shop without special circumstances. As soon as we closed the shop, they [ the villagers ] got even more flustered. "

The person who does not let lv Qunzhi close a shop is and exuberant, he is the village committee director of Yuhu village. In this epidemic, 31-year-old and vigorous with more than a dozen village cadres, in the medical supplies are extremely scarce, always stand in the front line of prevention and control.

On the evening of January 30, southern weekend journalists held talks with he exuberant. His Mandarin is not standard, but his words are sincere.

"I don't know what to say, I know our motherland is now difficult everywhere, but I as a village head (village committee director) , I want to protect my village. "

The following is a self-description by the village director:

1
Every door closed

1

###Every door closed

After I graduated from university, I first went to the scenic area to start a business, and then returned to the village after more than three years. On May 25,2016, I took part in a village poll and was elected village director.

Our village is rich in resources, but the advantages of resources are disadvantages. Because the village is located at the foot of Jade Dragon Snow Mountain, Mid-Levels, is the water conservation of the whole Lijiang, protected by the state, so many resources can not be developed, only for eco-tourism.

There are more than 1,600 aborigines in the village, as well as some out-of-town friends who came here to rent a courtyard for a bed and breakfast. They can't go back now. Altogether, there are more than 1,800 people. We natives are Nakhi people, and I am Nakhi people.

Our village has been doing basic tourism services, such as horseback riding, farmhouses, and bed and breakfast hotels. Some villagers do cleaning at bed-and-breakfast hotels, while others drive tour buses and commercial vehicles to earn some fares. Eighty percent of the people in the village work as tour attendants.

Baisha, Taishan is a 15-minute drive from Yuhu village and Lijiang is 20 minutes away. Because it's close to the city, and it's a tourist center, and we're really nervous. There are now six cases in Lijiang, all from friends visiting from Hubei, and the chances of contact in our village are too high.

Until January 25th, we were still in high spirits and everyone was thinking about the new year. On the 25th, the town called and asked us to start checking for anyone who had returned from the hot spots.

We find students coming back from there, we talk to them, and they come forward and they're quarantined in their homes. They were asked to take their temperature three times a day and report it to the village committee, which in turn reported it to their superiors. No patients have been found in the village.

There were tourists from Hubei, Guangdong, Hunan, Shanghai and Shenzhen in the village, so we tried to persuade them to go home for the Spring Festival. Later, the Lijiang City government deployed different hotels for Hubei and non-hubei residents. We'll escort all the "foreign" tourists.

The settlements are safer, there are medical staff, disinfection measures, but nothing in the village. We are a tourist city, and the government's protection for "foreigners" is the best, but it often leaves locals behind.

Also from the 25th, the village began to close the village, no longer receive guests. But the village is still in danger. Because of the incubation period of the disease, it is not yet possible to fully guarantee safety. On the day we closed the village, we had contact with people from Hubei Province.

Now no one in the village comes out. Every door closed, watching TV at home.

The villagers are in a state of polarization. Some people are particularly sensitive, but some villagers who work at home are particularly unafraid. I don't know why he wasn't scared. They said, "it's not going to come up here. The air is so good. ". Among those who are not afraid, those from poor families are in the majority.

2
"There's almost nothing in the village now. "

2

###"There's almost nothing in the village now. "

In the past, we sent villagers to the city to buy masks. Some people bought some at the drugstore, but now none of them can be bought. To tell the truth, we don't have any smog here, the air quality is very good, so we are very strange to the mask, never use. When we went to the drug company, it was mostly sold out by the city people.

The village clinic was down to a bottle or two of alcohol and a few small packets of disposable face masks for the medical staff.

The other day, we were trying to figure out our own way, and some of us were streaking into battle. On the 27th, we can not buy masks, everyone is to rely on their own relationship, to buy good friends, relatives. The masks are thin, and although I'm afraid they won't work, I have to wear them, or we'll all become cross-contamination and carry the virus around.

I'm wearing a disposable mask. One Mask, three days. Come back every day with a spritz of alcohol. Alcohol was given to me by my sister, who used to be a beautician. She had a bottle at home and gave it to me. I go to every pharmacy in Lijiang every day, but I can't get one.

Village Prevention and control work is the most difficult point in the equipment, which is difficult in the mask.

At a short meeting of our working group, it was said, we are not afraid of death, but we are concerned about the family behind us. I don't care if I die, but the family stays in the house, and we're going back after work. Everyone has only one home, and there is no way to live in the village committee. So, until we get home, we're GONNA have to spray it with alcohol.

Today, the Baisha, Taishan Town government handed out 20 N95 masks and 10 bags of disinfectant to the village committee. There are 9 people working in the village committee and 10 people working in the working group. One person is assigned to work at the entrance of the village. The village's tourism co-ops, commissaries, and the village council's service areas are all to be disinfected.

Sending a letter for help, it was a friend's suggestion. I actually want to ask him whether there is a channel to buy, I calculated a sum, because the village committee does not have money, to buy only twenty thousand yuan, too much not to guarantee, or to ask for funds from the boss. If we try, I'm worried, too, because the center of gravity is now in Wuhan.

I'm torn. As a village committee director, I have the obligation to protect our village first, but my ability is also limited, so very tangled.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Propaganda banners displayed by the Yuhu Village Committee. (photo / photo provided by interviewees)

3
Say "three DOTS. "

3

###Say "three DOTS. "

On January 25, the village implemented a "soft closure village. ". We set up a service point at the main entrance of the village, where the village committee cadres were stationed, and village cars had to be registered when they went out; no other cars were allowed except village cars.

On that day, the village tourism co-operative also closed down. The CO-OP has been in operation for more than a decade. Every household in the village has a horse for a basic horse-riding tour. Every day, one person from each family goes to the CO-OP. So the contact rate in our village is too high. We fear that if there is one case, the whole village will be affected, because more than 90% of the villagers have already touched each other.

I am also worried that some people even if it is a cold, fever, now it is not clear whether the new pneumonia. To tell the truth, there are too many people with colds in our area because it is very cold. And we can't get them. They're all sold out.

The whole country is surrounded by Hubei Wuhan, I really fear that if the outbreak in the village, it will be trouble. Lately, I've been staying up late.

We urge the grocery store not to close because they, too, are afraid and want to. But we're worried that when it's closed, people's lives will be disrupted. So I spent every day thinking about where to buy a mask, and I was willing to pay for a few at the grocery store.

Yuhu village is divided into nine groups, each group has a village leader. When doing prevention work, group leader Builds wechat group to householder, say the harm of new crown pneumonia ceaselessly in group. In our local parlance, "the three points, " as the head of the Baisha, Taishan Township Government taught us:

"The first is that the disease can be transmitted from person to person, during the incubation period. The second is that there is no cure for the disease. The third is that people may die from the disease. "

We went straight to them and said that it was much better now that there were very few people walking about in the village.

But a few days ago, I was very worried, because the villagers feel that the New Year is important. We ethnic minority areas in the traditional aspect and too rigid, must visit the elderly, so we are more pressure. Ordinary People's words are that, "people live is to make a love" . Sometimes we don't know what to tell him. We just say, "If you're dead, we'll never see you again. ". That's all we can say.

My family of seven people, Grandma more than 80 years old, aunt miss old mother, want to come to New Year, I told them not to come, with video new year. I said, "I'm the chief. Start with me. ". We were only a few kilometers away, but I didn't take them home or let my family out of the House.

I am especially grateful to my family for understanding me. At first, they told me, "you go around by yourself, "and if you come back with the virus, you're gonNA infect the whole family, or don't you come back? "? They finally let me go home. When I go home, is to take off clothes in the doorway, daughter-in-law for me to prepare a small bottle of alcohol, let me go spray.

In addition to online promotion, we also hang banners, broadcast. The village radio, recorded in the vernacular, played on a loop, telling everyone how to prevent it.

The village of two medical staff has been in the infirmary, to the village of cold people check, busy from morning to night. There are no designated hospitals in Baisha, Taishan for new pneumonia, only Yulong Naxi Autonomous County and Lijiang. All patients are now under quarantine at Lijiang People's Hospital.

Now, our Party branch is carrying out another work. Because there are more than 100 party members in the village, they are asked to assign tasks to party members, Group leaders and Party branch secretaries. Party members are asked to link up with farmers. Each party member is responsible for three farmers to do propaganda. I suggest they use mobile phone communication, wechat or make phone calls to avoid more cross-infection. I don't let them visit because no one has effective protection.

The area of our village is 36.7 square kilometers, and we walk around it for at least an hour. Because we are at the foot of the snow-capped mountains, the water is good, the air is good, many guests feel that we are very safe here, all run to avoid. But as far as I'm concerned, there's no safe zone.

There were some problems the other day. During the day, the village is closed, but some tourists park their cars in the woods outside the village and then come in on foot and hide in the village. These people, we find them, we send them to the camps. I and a few people of the village Party secretary patrol every day, checking every home.

4
$600,000 a day

4

###$600,000 a day

From about 2003, Yuhu village began to develop tourism. At present, the village receives about 200,000 visitors a year. Among them, there are 300 to 400 tourists a day in the tourism cooperative, plus the guests received by the village bed-and-breakfast and self-driving tourists.

The Spring Festival and the National Day Golden Week are the peak of tourism in the village. During the Spring Festival, there is snow in Jade Dragon Snow Mountain, and many people come here to admire it.

But this Spring Festival, the new pneumonia epidemic on our village had a greater impact. The village is now open for bed-and-breakfast 8, before the Spring Festival has been booked up, until the tenth day, all full room. But we've been trying to talk them out of it since eighth grade. 80%-90% of the villagers are engaged in tourism, under normal circumstances, they began to work after the first two days of the Lunar New Year, but this year, all stay at home.

So far this Spring Festival, the village's economic losses have been about 3 million (since January 26-30) .

The big part is the AIRBNB, which costs about five hundred thousand a day. Some of the more high-end bed-and-breakfast, a night room price is 5800 yuan, the lowest bed-and-breakfast is 1280 yuan, the average down the loss of bed-and-breakfast in more than 3000 yuan / night, a home has more than 20 rooms.

The other part is the villagers'loss. There are 400 families in the village who raise and rent horses. Each family can earn 100 yuan a day, which is 40,000 yuan a day. There are also more than 100 coaches in the village, such as 500 yuan a day, which adds up to 50,000 yuan. Together with the loss of catering, a day profit of about 500 yuan, three is 1500 yuan.

All this adds up to about $600,000 a day in the village.

2019 Spring Festival, the daily revenue is almost this number, from the first day to the seventh day, a day to receive 1000-1500 people. The number of visitors this year was up 10% from last year.

At its current level of development, Yuhu belongs to the upper middle class in the countryside of Lijiang. Because we all rely on tourism, while many other villages rely on fruits and vegetables. But we are also about 2700 meters above sea level, land can not grow, can only rely on tourism.

Before January 26, more than 1,000 tourists visited the village every day, and nearly 30,000 people were received throughout January. Tourists come from all over the country, travel agencies, self-driving tour, accommodation, meals, there are hiking hiking hiking hiking hiking.

The good news is that we have been in touch with the Hubei tourists since they were sent to the settlement, and none of them has been ill yet.
